rs fought against canned plots and moral simplicity, they participated in the evolution of the exhilarating new auteur television while underscoring the fact that art and entertainment don't have to be mutually exclusive. Nochimson also makes provocative distinctions between true auteur television and shows that were inspired by the freedom of the auteur series but nonetheless remained entrenched within the parameters of formula. Providing opportunities for vigorous discussion, Television Rewired will stimulate debates about which of the new television series since 1990 constitute “art” and which are tweaked “business-driven storytelling.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aTelevision authorshipzUnited States. 0aTelevision producers and directorszUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 0aTelevision producers and directorszUnited StatesxHistory andcriticism. 0aTelevision serieszUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 0aTelevision writerszUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/75944240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477318478423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477318478/original  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK